data.enText: to make an action or a process possible or easier

data.chText: 新贸易协定应当会加快经济发展。
data.enText: The new trade agreement should facilitate more rapid economic growth.

data.chText: 有条理的教导有利于学习。

simple_means.memory_skill: facil〔e〕容易做的 + it + ate 使… → 使容易

example: you could facilitate the process by sharing your knowledge
The stimulus facilitates a delayed impulse
This will help to prevent accidents

value.def: To facilitate an action or process, especially one that you would like to happen, means to make it easier or more likely to happen.

example.ex: The new airport will facilitate the development of tourism...
example.tran: 新机场将促进旅游业的发展。

example.ex: He argued that the economic recovery had been facilitated by his tough stance.
example.tran: 他认为他的强硬立场推动了经济的复苏。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to do, to make 做, 制作
rootsaffixes.title: fac, fact, feas, fect, fic(i), fig
